EU PETROL AND HEATING OIL PRICES UP ON OCTOBER 21

from EUROPE ENERGY, 25 October 1996, No. 478

All categories of EU fuel and heating oil prices rose between October 7
and October 21, according to figures from the European Commission's Energy
Directorate-General (DGXVII). Continuing a four-week trend, the average
price of premium-grade petrol rose slightly from ECU 216.92/1,000 litres
to ECU 220.61/1,000 litres, Euro-super unleaded premium-grade was up to
ECU 232.46/1,000 litres from ECU 227.30/1,000 litres, and motor diesel
jumped to ECU 251.14/1,000 litres from ECU 238.60/1,000 litres. Heating
oil prices increased to ECU 221.41/1,000 litres from ECU 219.50/1,000
litres (and rose as high as ECU 225.58/1,000 litres on October 14), and
residual fuel oil prices were up to ECU 123.99 from ECU 119.83 per 1,000
litres on average.

