PORVOO REFINERY POWER PLAN

Neste's board of directors has approved plans by the Neste oil refinery
at Porvoo to invest FM72m ($17m) in 1996 to build two to three 70-110
MW gas-fired power plants, Neste Porvoo's general manager Jouko
Huumonen said.

The plan, which was first proposed in June 1994, would involve the
phased development of on-site power generation capacity to supply oil
and petrochemical refining units at Porvoo.

According to Huumonen, Neste hoped to develop the small station concept
and have plants with a total generating capacity of 500-800 MW on site
by the year 2002. Excess production would be channelled into the
national grid.



