Nevada's De Vaux Power is promoting the "engine

Nevada's De Vaux Power is promoting the "engine
technology breakthrough of the century," an
internal combustion powerplant configured to
produce zero emissions, without pollution
controls, "by virtue of the amount of dwell we
are able to induce." Today's conventional engines
are based on a faulty engineering premise, De
Vaux says. Thomas Denner, 702-565-4829; fax same.




