January 5, 1996

BSM NAME SAD COORDINATOR

Once again, the Brazilian steel mills have nominated Helio Sad of
Usiminas as the chief negotiator for this year's coking coal contracts.
Talks are expected to start in late February after Carnival.

It should be noted that although the mills do much of their negotiating
as a bloc, the recent moves of CST to modify or cancel existing
contracts were the actions of that company on its own.



<A HREF ="#HeadList">Back to Headline List</A><BR>
