SHELL RINGS THE CHANGES

Shell Coal International has replaced Peter de Wit in his position as
vice president, supply and trading, with Mike Sweeney, previously
general manager for Asia, America and for metallurgical coal. De Wit
moves to a new post involving coal and gas supplies.

Meanwhile, in Australia, Shell is advertising for two traders. One is
to join its Shell Australia team in Sydney under Lindsay Flint, the
other to work with David Heap, the Shell Coal International executive
based there. The latter is effectively a relocation of a London-based
job, probably to Sydney or Jakarta.



