INTERNATIONAL COAL REPORT via NewsNet
January 5, 1996

RUHRKOHLE HOPES TO INCREASE STAKE IN GERMAN CREEK

Ruhrkohle International, a subsidiary of Ruhrkohle Handel, the trading
arm of German coal producer Ruhrkohle, wants to increase its share in
Australia's German Creek from around 12% to at least 20%.

Ruhrkohle International continues to scout the world for other
interesting investment possibilities. Any acquisitions are likely to be
small however after the investment of several hundred million DMs in
Venezuela since "Ruhrkohle is not a company with enormous financial
resources." Only those of the German state.



