INTERNATIONAL COAL REPORT via NewsNet
January 5, 1996

BF IRON OUTPUT SLOWS

Latest International Iron and Steel Institute blast furnace iron
production figures show a sharp drop off in November in European
activity rates. Indeed the institute's monthly analysis for the first
11 months of 1995 indicates a slowing across the board of the 43
industries surveyed. Although in Asia South Korea and Taiwan continue
to show growth, India, and significantly, Japan are both down - the
latter by 5.9% in November compared with November 1994.



