FINDS ADD 75 BCM OF GAS

Hydrocarbons were found in 64% of wells drilled on Norway's continental
shelf last year but most were small, according to state oil and gas
company Statoil. Proven reserves are put at roughly 320m bbls of oil
and 75 Bcm of natural gas, it said. Figures are provisional as some of
the biggest finds have yet to complete testing.



