<A NAME = "57"></A>Copyright
INTERNATIONAL GAS REPORT via NewsNet
January 5, 1996

SANTOS TESTS RECORD GAS FLOW

Santos Ltd said its Pennie-l well in the South Australia Patchawarra
East Block flowed 18.9 MMcfd of gas on test, the highest flow rate ever
recorded from the Cooper Basin. The Pennie well, located about 12.5 km
south of the Cuttapiria oil and gas field and 118 km north of the
Moomba gas plant, flowed gas from Permian Epsilon Formation sands at
2,849-2,868 metres depth on a 3/4-inch surface choke. The well was
first test of a number of undrilled prospects in the area, two of which
are due to be drilled this year, said Santos.



