INTERNATIONAL GAS REPORT via NewsNet
January 5, 1996

NGC BUYS OKEENE GAS-GATHERING SYSTEM

USA - NGC has bought Oneok's OKeene gas-gathering system in Oklahoma.
NGC plans to install central compression on the 180 mile system,
enabling field-gathering pressures to be reduced.

It can then be consolidated into the low-pressure Ringwood and Rodman
systems already owned by NGC. Costs will thus be reduced, while well
productivity could be boosted.



