derrick extension.  The rig is planned to be available in the North Sea
from March 1996.  The Transocean Seeker is due in the North Sea at the
beginning of February at the end of its journey from the Far East.  It
too is still available and is expected to enter the market in April.

Elsewhere in the market, the Ocean Alliance is due out of the Cromarty
Firth at the weekend to return to work for BP, while the Sedco 704 is
due in the Firth for survey work before resuming operations for Shell
on the Gannet Field as a drilling tender.

Northwest European jack-up drilling rig utilisation dipped slightly at
the end of 1995 with the release of the Rowan California by Phillips
Petroleum in the UK and the entry of the Ensco 70 to the Verolme yard
in Holland for upgrading.  The Ensco jack-up is due to return to work
for NAM at the end of February equipped with a new 15,000 psi BOP stack
among other improvements.  The California is stacked off Great Yarmouth
until the end of January when it is due to mobilise for Wintershall in
Holland.



