NESTE OFFLOADS 50% STAKE IN SOVEREIGN EXPLORATION

Following the completion of the sale of its UK oil assets to Sands
Petroleum, Neste has agreed to sell its 50% share in Sovereign
Exploration to Northgas, a subsidiary of Northern Electric.  Early in
1994 Neste and Northern Electric formed an upstream gas company based
on Neste's southern basin interests including the Victor Field.  In
addition to Victor, Sovereign currently has holdings in the Schooner
Field, due on stream at the end of this year, and the Windermere
development.



